description: Follow Dana on her misadventures in and around the comic convention scene. It's a fast and furious look at the quirky characters of the comic community and their rivalries, where the battles are so bitter because the stakes are so small. Dramatic license has been taken with the con goings-ons, but the content will still have you nodding in ruthless agreement.

description: In the tradition of Knights of the Dinner Table and Dork Tower, Nodwick chronicles the comic adventures of a medieval, adventuring threesome and their henchman. In this issue, our heroes are hired to find the lost Temple of Skizzopreen. Unfortunately for Nodwick the henchman, his companions will require him to endure avalanches, nymphomaniacal priestesses, and a dragon with a penchant for explosives.

This issue finds our heroes embarking on a quest to save the Henchmen's Graveyard from plunder by a rogue henchman and a trio of black-clad villains. What's worse, the bad guys are some of the most powerful adventurers around! Nodwick and his friends must resort to using brains to best these foes.

Nodwick #3 Print-and-webcomic by Aaron Williams, the same author as PS238 and Full Frontal Nerdity. Focuses on what can only be called a misadventuring group in a fantasy world based loosely on Dungeons And Dragons settings. The party consists of a less than worldly cleric named Piffany; a completely expendable henchman, the titular Nodwick; a power-hungry wizard named Artax; and a brawler named Yeagar. The print comic followed a story arc concerning the party's battle with an evil god called Baphuma'al, while at the same time the online variant and its apperances in Dragon Magazine provided shorter a-gag-a-week stories that were unrelated to the goings-on of the print story.

Nodwick #4 Print-and-webcomic by Aaron Williams, the same author as PS238 and Full Frontal Nerdity. Focuses on what can only be called a misadventuring group in a fantasy world based loosely on Dungeons And Dragons settings. The party consists of a less than worldly cleric named Piffany; a completely expendable henchman, the titular Nodwick; a power-hungry wizard named Artax; and a brawler named Yeagar. The print comic followed a story arc concerning the party's battle with an evil god called Baphuma'al, while at the same time the online variant and its apperances in Dragon Magazine provided shorter a-gag-a-week stories that were unrelated to the goings-on of the print story.

"The 13th Edition": What would happen if someone tried to dominate all magic everywhere by imposing the use of a flawed operating system? Well, after trying the system a few times (and surviving the resulting disasters), Artax and his friends set off to stop Macroscoff's plan to make the 13th Edition Magic System the dominant (and only) way to use magic. Can they stop this monolithic company? Can their demonic lawyers be defeated? Can they count on the help of a wizard who casts spells using multi-colored apples? Will we get sued by someone currently in trouble with the Justice Department? This issue features an awesome cover by acclaimed artist Tony DiTerlizzi!

"There will be only me!" That's the cry that heralds Nodwick's head being lopped off... for the 20th time. Those pesky immortals have surfaced on the land of Nodwick, and it's up to our favorite henchman's pals to help him survive the head- harvest. Why are these sword-waving people coming after a mere henchman? Can Artex and Yeagar resist the temptation of attaining immortality themselves? Should Piffany give up the duct tape and switch to Velcro? Read Nodwick #6 for the answers to these, and many more nagging questions.

"The Wind in the Pillows": Our heroes have gone on some pretty strange quests before, but this one might top them all! Deep in a forgotten wizard's tower, behind deadly traps lies... a pillow! Yeah, but it's no "ordinary" pillow! At least, that's what the people who come after it seem to think. What is this bedroom accessory's secret? Can Nodwick and the gang find out before it falls into the wrong hands?

What happens when the powers running the cosmos make a major mistake and give god-like powers to those who can't be trusted with sharp objects? Find out when Yeagar discovers he can fly, bend steel in his bare hands, and leap piles of hirelings in a single bound. Will his compatriots join his Legion of Superb Heroes, or will they convince him to find some way to hang up his cape?

"A World Without Piffany": What would the world of Nodwick be like without our favorite font of goodness, purity and virtue? Nodwick finds out when he falls into the Cleft of the Cosmos and finds himself in a most ugly reality; Henchmen are extinct, evil rules the land, and the person who duct-tapes him back from the grave has never existed! Meanwhile, back in Nodwick's home universe, things aren't much better because Piffany's superiors think it's time for her to retire from adventuring and take up more academic pursuits! Pick up Nodwick #9 for part one of this two-part epic! Plus, brand-new back- up strips: Dork Tower by John Kovalic and PvP by Scott Kurtz!

A World Without Piffany: Part II: Ever have one of those days when you cross into a parallel universe where birds never sing, the sun never shines, and the luckiest people are the ones who've been listed in the obituaries? Nodwick has. He has to escape the evil versions of his former employers, find a way back to his dimension of origin and convince Piffany's superiors to let her keep adventuring with Artax and Yeagar. If he fails, his homeworld may get the doomsday treatment, too! Can Nodwick survive this ordeal without Piffany and her duct tape? Nodwick #10 holds the answers you seek!

"Dungeon Crawl": Yeagar is a simple man: Sally forth, kill stuff, take the loot, spend it on ale, repeat. Lately, his life's been just a little too complicated, so he and his valiant companions (yes, and Nodwick, too!) embark on a simple dungeon denizen extermination mission. But hark! What's this? Our simple delving into the depths is in danger of running into... plot devices! Can Yeagar manage to keep a little diversion into mindless hack-'n'-slashing from turning into an epic tale of cunning, skill, and heroics (not to mention tedious thought, planning, and forethought)!

Just in time for the holidays, it's a tale of yuletide... uh, death, actually. Will Nodwick return to the Land of the Living after yet another tragic adventuring "accident," or will he listen to the angels that are trying to convince him to pass beyond the veil for good? Also, read the epic tale of one adventuring group (Nodwick and company, of course) as they take on 13th Century Realty and the Hollow of Hazardous Horror!

"Chains of Love": Never have romantic relations with your employees, especially if they're henchmen. Piffany tries her best not to break this cardinal rule, but something's compelling her to lay a smooch on one grapefruit-schnozzed hireling named Nodwick! But that's not all! What's the terrible secret that Piffany has been keeping about her love life? Why has she never pursued a romantic interest before, and why might the fate of the world ride on it? Pick up Nodwick #13, and read this Valentine's Day tale for yourself!

"Landlords of the Realm." As all Nod-o-Philes will recall, our heroes recently came into possession of a dungeon of their own, the famed "Hollow of Hazardous Horror." What they didn't know is that it's in a covenant neighborhood. If they don't get its evil quotient up to specs, the bank will foreclose on not only the dungeon, but on the owners' house! Can Yeagar change his skills to monster capturing rather than slaying? Can Artax find any magical solution to entice malevolent beasties into living in the Hollow? Can Piffany bring herself to make someplace more evil? Will Nodwick escape being used as creature bait?

"Tournamental Health": The king is dying, and he's putting on the most extreme jousting tourney ever devised before he goes. He's invited some extraordinarily destructive contestants to enter, and Yeagar has made the cut! Luckily, the rules for knocking opponents off their horses have several loopholes large enough to march a chariot through, so don't expect the usual men on mere horses to mar the field of honor! Can Yeagar pull a victory out of the mayhem? Will his equipment survive the abuse? Can Artax and Piffany remain on the sidelines? What ultimate prize will go to the victor? Find out in Nodwick #15!

Yeagar has won the powerful Gauntlet of Supremacy, and it looks like his adventuring career can't go anywhere but up. However, the history of the artifact seems to be strewn with lots of nasty deaths, catastrophe and eventual insanity. Will our heroes be able to stop the curse and free Yeagar from its grip before he launches a world domination tour? Piffany has a plan, but for it to succeed, she and her companions have to delve into Yeagar's very soul! All this and more in the pages of Nodwick #16!

And you thought fixing foreign cars was complicated. How about trying to extract an evil artifact from someone's very essence? Nodwick, Piffany, and Artax are on a metaphysical "Fantastic Voyage" into Yeagar's soul to free him from the Gauntlet of Supremacy before it drives him bonders. Will they succeed, or will their former comrade be doomed to run rampant leaving they world in ruins?

"Grim Fairy Tales": Adventuring in a land of dragons, fairies, and magic should be the norm for our heroes, but something seems amiss when they find themselves dealing with Sleeping Beauties, Trolls under bridges, and gnomes that can spin straw into gold! Will Nodwick and company escape this land of fantasy and return to their own? And who's behind their farcical fairy tale, anyway? Pick up Nodwick #18 and find out!

"Krutz": Witness that rarest of events: the birth of a new cuss-word! Yes, friends, "krutz" is the answer to your every vulgarity need, be it adjective, adverb, verb, noun, whatever! "Krutz" can do it all! But what's this? Does "krutz" come with a price? Will too much "krutz"-ing lead to world-dooming events? Can Piffany's anti-krutz crusade save Yeagar from having a one-word vocabulary?
Artax prizes knowledge of magic, and thanks to an ancient artifact, he's going to get more than he bargained for. Will Artex give up his life and his friends for the power of omniscience?

The Orb of Omniscience has been uncovered! This mighty object allows the user to know everything about everything, and gives them a little cognitive boost in the process. In this issue, the fight over the Orb continues, but with a little hitch in everyone's plans: It seems to have fallen into the hands of our heroes' latest inept employee: Nitwick the henchman!

Thanks to the Orb of Omniscience, our heroes have located Rowen, a woman who plays a mysterious role in Yeagar's past. Unfortunately, she's up to her sword-hilt in trouble. A mysterious creature haunts the adventurer's guild, and it's taken a shine to one of its members.

Nodwick has come into possession of a legendary band of metal. Can he get rid of it before becoming a victim of countless orcs, dwarves, elves, and a myriad of other weirdos with a hankering for this one ring? See LOTR skewered as it has never been before!

Nodwick and company go on a sea monster hunt! Some horned helmeted people have hired them to stop this plague upon their seafaring, but are the heroes up to the challenge? Do henchmen make good sea serpent bait? Will they need a bigger boat?

Nodwick and the gang meet the most mysterious people in this issue! It's the shadowy "Clergy in Black." They have a mission for our destructive daring-doers upon which the fate of the world hinges...eventually. Prophecy and peril await!

Our heroes are sent to a very remote monastery to safeguard a very unique magical artifact, but the forces of evil are out to get it as well! Can our stalwart-if-clueless band open up a cask of whoop-hinder on the attacking army of horrors? Read Nodwick #26 and find out!

Someone's kidnapping all the henchmen! From all over the land, toters of loot and haulers of swag are vanishing! Will adventurers have to stoop to lugging their own treasure, or is there some more nefarious scheme afoot? And is Nodwick himself safe from this purging of the employment rolls?

Long ago, the gods decided that the Tree of Knowledge was making the inhabitants of the Earth a little too full of themselves. The only remaining part of that tree forms the mystic "Clue-By-Four," a divine plank of power that can up the smarts of anyone hit in the head with it. In this issue, Nodwick and company cross paths with it, and they'll need all the smarts they can get to stop the havoc it wreaks! Pick up Nodwick #28, and give your I.Q. a whack!

Ever have one of those days when something seems... missing? An evil force has taken away some of the "bits" making up the world, leaving only eight! Can our heroes win through in an 8-bit tribute to RPG video games and other console horrors of ages past?

What army... er, band of warriors... er, guys who work for the forces of good would be complete without a genuine dragon mount? Nodwick would sure like to find out, since the care and feeding of the beast has fallen to him! Care isn't so bad. Feeding can be, especially when your charge discovers you're delicious! Can Nodwick survive to the final battle with Baphuma'al if this addition to the group sticks around? Can he get a good deal on Dragon Chow? Cover art by Frank Cho!

The great Nitwick hunt is on! Our heroes know he's got something that could determine the fate of the world, but where to find the world's most worthless henchman? And what are they willing to do to get what he has? Join Nodwick and the gang (and their new pet Dragon) as the medieval mirth and mayhem continue!

The final battle against an evil god of dark magic has begun, and it's in Nodwick's home town! Our heroes have to find a way to breach their town's defenses without giving a passage to the horde of unspeakable creatures laying siege to Krutzing Hollow!

Whoops! After taking a hit from the Gauntlet of Supremacy, Yeagar finds himself teetering between life and afterlife! Can Piffany and her fellow clerics bring him back to the land of the living? How will his friends fare against Baphuma'al without his sword to aid them? And will the Fang & Flagon go out of business without its most intoxicated patron?

The war for Krutzing Hollow is on! The armies of evil, previously trying to keep our heroes out, are now trying to get themselves in! And who will be there to save the day? Well, it looks like a cleric riding a hamster with the power to fly, among other things. And how has a gazebo become the central focus in the war between light and dark? All this and more, as the final battle with Baphuma'al continues!

To the Victor Goes... the Gazebo!

He who rules the universe will first rule . . . the gazebo? The final battle between good and icky-badness is nearing its climax as the struggle for a nexus of power has shifted its location to a pavilion in a public park. Can Nodwick and his friends defend the public from Baphuma'al and his army of monstrosities? Don't miss this dose of medieval hilarity and struggle for festive wooden structures everywhere!

The story of Nodwick is a classic tale of boy meets party, boy hires on with party, boy becomes injured, crushed, punctured, smelted, flattened, stapled, eaten, and occasionally used to carry stuff. A young henchman seeks his fortune and unwittingly contracts himself to a trio of adventurers who constantly rewrite the book on legendary exploits (mostly under chapters beginning with the word "don't"). They have defeated evil tyrants, slain rampaging monsters, looted ruined cities (often doing the ruining themselves, saving time), and generally brought adventure to those who would otherwise live peaceful lives. No job is too small for these heroes, primarily because they are often broke, bored, or both. Unfortunately, the outcome of their adventures is rarely positive for anyone involved, and many are the hamlets that would sooner face an outbreak of intestinal warts than lodge these "heroes" for a fortnight.

The Evil Wed(ding)

It's the last battle with Baphuma'al, so we're going out with. . . a wedding? Have our heroes finally met their match as this god of dark magic wrests victory from the forces of good? Will Piffany have any bridesmaids at her nuptials? And just who is she marrying anyway? Pick up Nodwick 36 as this epic story arc comes to a close! And don't miss this one since Nodwick will be going on hiatus in 2007!
